articles.title: AGS, tick-borne meat allergy, has puts thousands of Americans at risk - USA TODAY
articles.description: More than 110,000 suspected cases of alpha-gal syndrome, caused by ticks, were identified between 2010 and 2022, according to the CDC.
articles.content: As many as 450,000 people in the United States may have been affected by alpha-gal syndrome (AGS), the Center of Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) announced Thursday. AGS, also known as the red-me… [+4065 chars]
